    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1858"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1858">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.3111/40.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Venezuelan Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am shocked and grieved to learn of the lamentable death of Senor Rojas and I
                    hasten to extend to you an expression of my profound sympathy.</p>
                <p>The Department would like to consult with you with a view to making arrangements
                    for the funeral service, and to affording you every possible assistance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
